kitty-launcher (0.5.5-1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Release: bump to 0.5.5
  * Include documentation and packaging version updates

  * Add --path/-p short form for set working directory
  * Add session creation with embedded cwd directive
  * Auto-detect current working directory when --path/-p not specified
  * In -l/--create-launcher, prompt to create session if not found
  * Inject cwd into session file, not desktop file
  * Add prompt for overwrite, warn about shadowing
  * Pass WKSPC_ROOT env var to kitty child processes
  * Update default template to use WKSPC_ROOT tabs
  * Rename template from z-tools.session to kitty.session-template
  * Copy template as-is, only inject directive if -p explicitly provided

 -- OpenCode Contributors <contributors@opencode.ai>  Wed, 06 May 2026 12:00:00 +0000

kitty-launcher (0.5.2-1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Add session file directive parsing (#%[ key = value ]%# syntax)
  * Add currentWorkingDir directive to set kitty startup directory via -d flag
  * Add expand_tilde() helper for ~ expansion in directive values
  * Update default session template with directive usage example
  * Update help output with SESSION DIRECTIVES documentation section
  * Add 9 new unit tests covering directive parsing and tilde expansion

